Title: check_traceroute: Support for IPv6
Level: 1
Component: checks
Compatible: compat
Edition: cre
Version: 2.0.0i1
Date: 1568894217
Class: feature

The active check for traceroute now supports IPv6. In the service parameters you can now specify the IP address familiy.
For link-local addresses (IP addresses starting with 'fe80') you may need to specify a zone/interface index or name by appending it with a % to the IP address (e.g. fe80::aebc:32ff:fe95:8ac1%eth0)
Otherwise this error might occur: 'connect: Invalid argument'
